ADDIS ABABA, Dec. 25 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has registered 4,573 new COVID-19 cases in the past 24 hours, taking the nationwide tally to 390,737 as of Friday evening, the country's health ministry said. The ministry reported three new COVID-19-related deaths and 632 recoveries, bringing the national counts to 6,888 and 352,025 respectively. Ethiopia, Africa's second-most populous nation, has so far reported the largest number of COVID-19 cases in the East Africa region. Over the past few days, the East African country is witnessing a spike in new COVID-19 cases. Amid its national push for vaccination, Ethiopia has administered 10,801,055 doses of COVID-19 vaccines, according to the ministry. Ethiopia is among the countries hardest hit by COVID-19 in Africa, following South Africa, Morocco, Tunisia and Libya.  Enditem